03/09/2004
PULA, Croatia -- The detention of former Macedonian Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski was extended for three more days Thursday (2 September), according to the Macedonian news agency MIA. Boskovski is being detained in Croatia on charges he organised the 2002 killing of seven immigrants from India and Pakistan, while he was interior minister. Boskovski, who is also a Croatian citizen, was arrested earlier this week. (MIA, HINA - 03/09/04)
